# Fix Missing config.toml Problem

If Runner continuously reports:

```text
Failed to load config stat
/etc/gitlab-runner/config.toml
```

Create file manually:

```bash
nano ~/gitlab_local_srv/runner/config/config.toml
```

Paste:

```toml
concurrent = 1
check_interval = 0
shutdown_timeout = 0

[session_server]
  session_timeout = 1800

[[runners]]
  name = "local-docker-runner"
  url = "https://gitlab.docker.loc"
  token = "PASTE_NEW_TOKEN_HERE"
  tls-ca-file = "/etc/gitlab-runner/certs/ca.crt"
  executor = "docker"

  [runners.cache]
    MaxUploadedArchiveSize = 0

  [runners.docker]
    tls_verify = false
    image = "ubuntu:22.04"
    privileged = false
    disable_entrypoint_overwrite = false
    oom_kill_disable = false
    disable_cache = false

    volumes = [
      "/cache",
      "/var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock",
      "/etc/docker/certs.d:/etc/docker/certs.d:ro"
    ]

    shm_size = 0
    network_mtu = 0
    network_mode = "gitlab_local_srv_gitlab-net"
```

Permissions:

```bash
sudo chown -R 100:101 runner/config

sudo chmod 600 \
runner/config/config.toml
```

Restart:

```bash
docker restart runner-loc
```

Verify:

```bash
docker logs runner-loc
```

Expected:

```text
Configuration loaded
Initializing executor providers
```

